Q.2 --> What are tags and attributes in HTML?

Ans:-
    
      -> HTML Tags:
 
      They are enclosed in angle brackets < > and typically come in pairs, consisting of an opening tag and a closing tag.
      Ex. <html>
          <head>
          <body>
          <meta> 
          <p>
          <a>
          <title>
          <div>
          <button> etc.. are tag of html.


       -> HTML Attributes: 

        Attributes are additional information provided within the opening tag of an HTML element. They are used to modify or specify characteristics and properties of an element.
        Ex. action
            align
            bgcolor
            border
            charset
            href
            width
            height  etc.. are attributes of html.

       
     